name.text: Free Philly Capoeira Classes
name.html: Free Philly Capoeira Classes

description.text:
Join us for an Intro of Capoeira! Capoeira is an ancient Afro-Brazilian Martial art full of rich cultural history. Embodied in DANCE, Capoeira perfectly blends self-defense, acrobatics, music, and culture. Training Capoeira builds full-body control while allowing you to create a dialogue through movement. 
Our special 120 minute intro workshop will focus on rhythm, musicality, balance, strength, and endurance. Please be prepared with comfortable clothing and a reusable water bottle. 

We ask that if you enjoy your first FREE class that you sign-up for our weekly classes scheduled Mon-Wed from 6pm - 8pm. 

Please invite friends and family who may be interested.

name.text: Dustin Douglas & The Electric Gentlemen
name.html: Dustin Douglas & The Electric Gentlemen

description.text:
Dustin Douglas & The Electric Gentlemen



Capturing the vibe of late 60’s and 70’s blues-laced rock-n- roll, Wilkes-Barre Pennsylvania’s premier power blues-rock trio, Dustin Douglas & The Electric Gentlemen mix retro-style and groove a-la (Jimi Hendrix Experience, Stevie Ray Vaughan, Led Zeppelin, Black Crowes) for a lightning charged, vintage style all their own.
Led by the transcendent lead guitarist/singer/songwriter Dustin Douglas (Lemongelli, The Badlees), The Electric Gentlemen (Tommy Smallcomb-Drums & Matt “The Dane” Gabriel-Bass) leave even the most discerning music fans with little left to ask for at the end of any live show!
Blues rock is often played badly but like any genre, there are those that can rise above the mediocrity and demonstrate a real flair. This album will give you only a glimpse of how strong this trio’s riveting live show is.  -Jim Hynes- Senior Writer – (Elmore Magazine)
